<HEADLINE>Windfall for ship</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>2</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974782493</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Historians were yesterday given nearly #1m of National Lottery cash to restore
one of the oldest ships in the world. The HMS Trincomalee Project in
Hartlepool, Cleveland, was one of 34 projects to collect a total of #25m from
the Heritage Lottery Fund.
</TEXT>
