<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<FLAG>Foreign digest</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974782600</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Film attacked
LOS ANGELES: The family of former US President Richard Nixon has denounced
controversial director Oliver Stone's new film, Nixon, as ``erroneous and
malicious''. Nixon's daughters Tricia Nixon Cox and Julie Nixon Eisenhower
accused Stone of character assassination of their late father.
Bodies found
ASUNCION: Up to 100 corpses, which Paraguayan police say may be those of
drug-traffickers or smugglers, have been found in a clandestine grave across
the border in Brazil. News reports say there were signs of torture.
Man impaled
KIEV: A timber yard worker survived a bizarre accident that left him impaled on
a 5ft wooden pole. Fellow workers had to saw off both ends and carry him to
hospital, where doctors took three hours to remove the pole.
</TEXT>
