<HEADLINE>Woman driver guilty of causing man's death</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974782660</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SUSAN MITCHELL, 28, a mother of three, was yesterday found guilty of causing a
drunken death smash which also left her boyfriend a virtual vegetable.
Mitchell, of Bruce Avenue, Dingwall, had denied causing the death of passenger
Ronald MacDonald, 34, of Strathpeffer, by careless driving while unfit through
drink.
She had also denied injuring another passenger, her boyfriend, insurance
representative Kevin Dennison, 30, who, the court heard, can now move only his
eyes. A third male passenger was slightly injured.
She was found guilty by a jury after a three-day trial.
Sheriff James Fraser deferred sentence on Mrs Mitchell until January 8 for
background reports.
Fiscal Ron Phillips likened the road tragedy to a festive season TV campaign
against drinking and driving, only this time ``nobody was acting''.
</TEXT>
