<DOCNO>GH951221-000113</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951221-000113</DOCID>
<DATE>951221</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Forward for Flyers</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>30</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974782662</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FIFE Flyers last night confirmed the signing of rugged Canadian forward Kevin
St Jacques.
The player, drafted by National Hockey League side Chicago, then loaned to
their farm team, Indianapolis, joins Scotland's only Premier Division club in
the New Year. Player-coach Mark Morrison confirmed the Kirkcaldy-based club had
applied for a work permit for the robust player, who is a prolific marksman and
also a big penalty taker.
Morrison said: ``We've heard great reports about Kevin and we don't anticipate
any hitches with his work permit.''
St Jacques led the scoring charts in the Western Hockey League in 1991-92
season with 140 points for Lethbridge and Morrison added: ``That level of
scoring would do us fine.''
</TEXT>
