<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>16</PAGE>
<FLAG>Correspondence</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>974782663</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MR GEORGE Galloway is the most fortunate of men: he has it in his power to
right a wrong. He can stand down as Labour candidate in Glasgow Kelvin and
nominate Mr Sarwar to take his place.
If only Mr Galloway had spoken up earlier in the same clear terms he used in
Bradford, the Scottish Labour Party could have been spared unseemly selection
squabbles in Kelvin as well as in Govan.
Christopher Mason,
Leader, Liberal Democrat Group, Strathclyde Regional Council.
</TEXT>
