<DOCNO>GH951221-000126</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951221-000126</DOCID>
<DATE>951221</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Oasis tipped to headline return of Balloch concerts</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>By SARAH URQUHART</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>974782675</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTLAND looks set to play host to some of the biggest names in the music
business next year.
Top group Oasis are believed to be considering headlining a huge outdoor
concert in Balloch Castle Country Park on the banks of Loch Lomond next summer.
Although details of the event have not been released, Edinburgh-based concert
promoters Regular Music are involved in talks with Dumbarton District Council.
Councillor Sam McCallum, convener of the Leisure Committee, said: ``I can't
name names at the moment, but we're hoping to land the biggest and the best for
Balloch.''
The Balloch Castle Country Park was the setting in June 1991 for a Runrig
concert.
It was also revealed yesterday that Scotlands biggest pop festival, in
Strathclyde Park, will go ahead next July.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
